¬†@Frozenkex¬† The main advantage of ER is that it gives players the opportunity to learn mechanics in a more realistic environment, can collect stronger items and have earlier access to co-op. I still think most of that hinges heavily upon relying upon guides to work, otherwise a new player might linger too long on inconsequential encounters and just abandon anything too difficult and not make any meaningful progression.
Asylum Demon has very long wind ups to their attacks, barely any multi hit combos and a pretty small health pool. Not to mention you get to knock off a chunk of its HP in the fall attack and have the option of black fire bombs if you really get stuck. I can see why people could stop at Asylum Demon, but the game is very generous and even though asylum demon is big, gameplay wise it's not too different from the hollows in the prison, it's a natural escalation in difficulty. In contrast, nothing in Limgrave prepares you for any of the boss battles in that region, no matter how much time you spend practicing on foot soldiers, none of them naturally lead into the challenge posed by Margit, The tomb Gargoyle, the cave beast, erdtree avatars or the Leonid at Morne.

¬†@Yoruzako¬† Sure, any game can be casual if you play casually; that wasn't quite my point. Let's compare Elden Ring to Street Fighter V.

You can play both games casually and have a blast; however, I would argue that if you want to get to the end of Elden Ring, you don't have to practice for months and learn the frame data of each of your attacks. SFV requires you to know the frame data of your character and how it stacks against a variety of other characters. Additionally, if you aren't practicing, you'll never reach the "end", which we can say is like top 10% of the rankings. THAT is competitive.

Elden Ring isn't easy by any stretch of the imagination (Margit kicked my ass back and forth for a solid 5 hours (not consecutive)), but it doesn't require an incredible amount of time-investment like competitive games to get good. Even playing casually you'll improve and get to the final boss.
